20after%20a%20maintenance%20alert%20went%20off%2C%20according%20to%20an%20incident%20report%20obtained%20by%20the%20AP%2C%20requiring%20the%20plane's%20captain%20to%20return%20to%20the%20gate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20passengers%20were%20unhappy%20and%20one%20of%20them%20opened%20the%20emergency%20door%20and%20stepped%20out%20on%20the%20wing%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20event%20required%20the%20plane%20to%20be%20changed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20Aeromexico%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20the%20first%20time%20a%20passenger%20has%20ventured%20onto%20a%20plane's%20wing%20or%20opened%20an%20emergency%20exit%20in%20recent%20months.%20In%20July%2C%20a%20passenger%20tried%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpassenger-opened-plane-emergency-door-mid-air-paris-bengaluru-india-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20open%20an%20AirFrance%20emergency%20exit%20midair%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20ensure%20it%20worked%20properly.%20He%20was%20arrested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20November%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouthwest-passenger-jumped-from-emergency-exit-tried-to-steal-truck-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20Southwest%20Airlines%20passenger%20jumped%20out%20of%20an%20emergency%20exit%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20attempted%20to%20steal%20a%20truck%20in%20Louisiana%2C%20causing%20panic%20among%20their%20fellow%20travelers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faeromexico-emergency-exit-wing-tarmac-delay-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706458134000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b67044ac2de4f17ee525b1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faeromexico-emergency-exit-wing-tarmac-delay-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dozens%20of%20passengers%20have%20signed%20a%20statement%2C%20handwritten%20on%20notebook%20paper%2C%20defending%20the%20man.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ledmonds%40businessinsider.com%20(Lauren%20Edmonds)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A50%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faeromexico-emergency-exit-wing-tarmac-delay-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NASA's%20Hubble%20Detects%20Water%20Vapour%20In%20Small%20Exoplanet's%20Atmosphere%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAstronomers%20using%20NASA's%20Hubble%20Space%20Telescope%20have%20detected%20water%20molecules%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20of%20a%20small%2Cblazing-hot%20exoplanet%2097%20light-years%20from%20Earth.%20The%20planet%2C%20named%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.nasa.gov%2Fmissions%2Fhubble%2Fnasas-hubble-finds-water-vapor-in-small-exoplanets-atmosphere%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EGJ%209827d%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20approximately%20twice%20Earth's%20diameter%20and%20could%20be%20an%20example%20of%20potential%20planets%20with%20water-rich%20atmospheres%20elsewhere%20in%20our%20galaxy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20would%20be%20the%20first%20time%20that%20we%20can%20directly%20show%20through%20atmospheric%20detection%2C%20that%20these%20planets%20with%20water-rich%20atmospheres%20can%20exist%20around%20other%20stars%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20team%20member%20Bjorn%20Benneke%20of%20the%20Trottier%20Institute%20for%20Research%20on%20Exoplanets%20at%20Universite%20de%20Montreal.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20an%20important%20step%20toward%20determining%20the%20prevalence%20and%20diversity%20of%20atmospheres%20on%20rocky%20planets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWater%20on%20a%20planet%20this%20small%20is%20a%20landmark%20discovery%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20co-principal%20investigator%20Laura%20Kreidberg%20of%20Max%20Planck%20Institute%20for%20Astronomy%20in%20Heidelberg%2C%20Germany.%20%26quot%3BIt%20pushes%20closer%20than%20ever%20to%20characterizing%20truly%20Earth-like%20worlds.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWater%20is%20essential%20for%20life%2C%20but%20the%20exoplanet%20is%20unlikely%20to%20host%20any%20type%20of%20life%20due%20to%20its%20searing%20temperatures%20that%20would%20turn%20a%20water-rich%20atmosphere%20into%20steam.%20However%2C%20astronomers%20have%20yet%20to%20uncover%20the%20truth%20of%20this%20unusual%20world's%20atmosphere.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20of%20the%20study%20appeared%20in%20a%20report%20published%20on%20Thursday%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiopscience.iop.org%2Farticle%2F10.3847%2F2041-8213%2Facebf0%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Astrophysical%20Journal%20Letters.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20the%20research%20team%20can't%20tell%20whether%20Hubble%20picked%20up%20on%20water%20vapour%20traces%20within%20a%20puffy%2C%20hydrogen-rich%20atmosphere%20or%20the%20planet%20has%20a%20water-rich%20atmosphere%20because%20the%20host%20star%20evaporated%20GJ%209827d's%20original%20hydrogen%20and%20helium%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20observing%20program%2C%20led%20by%20principal%20investigator%20Ian%20Crossfield%20of%20Kansas%20University%20in%20Lawrence%2C%20Kansas%2C%20was%20designed%20specifically%20to%20not%20only%20detect%20the%20molecules%20in%20the%20planet's%20atmosphere%20but%20to%20look%20specifically%20for%20water%20vapour.%20Either%20result%20would%20be%20exciting%2C%20whether%20water%20vapour%20is%20dominant%20or%20just%20a%20tiny%20species%20in%20a%20hydrogen-dominant%20atmosphere%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20science%20paper's%20lead%20author%2C%20Pierre-Alexis%20Roy%20of%20the%20Trottier%20Institute%20for%20Research%20on%20Exoplanets%20at%20Universite%20de%20Montreal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUntil%20now%2C%20we%20had%20not%20been%20able%20to%20directly%20detect%20the%20atmosphere%20of%20such%20a%20small%20planet.%20And%20we're%20slowly%20getting%20in%20this%20regime%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20Benneke.%20%26quot%3BAt%20some%20point%2C%20as%20we%20study%20smaller%20planets%2C%20there%20must%20be%20a%20transition%20where%20there's%20no%20more%20hydrogen%20on%20these%20small%20worlds%2C%20and%20they%20have%20atmospheres%20more%20like%20Venus%20(which%20is%20dominated%20by%20carbon%20dioxide).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBecause%20the%20planet%20is%20as%20hot%20as%20Venus%2C%20at%20800%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%2C%20it%20definitely%20would%20be%20an%20inhospitable%2C%20steamy%20world%20if%20the%20atmosphere%20were%20predominantly%20water%20vapour%2C%20NASA%20said%20in%20a%20release.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20present%20the%20team%20is%20left%20with%20two%20possibilities.%20One%20scenario%20is%20that%20the%20planet%20is%20still%20clinging%20to%20a%20hydrogen-rich%20atmosphere%20laced%20with%20water%2C%20making%20it%20a%20mini-Neptune.%20Alternatively%2C%20it%20could%20be%20a%20warmer%20version%20of%20Jupiter's%20moon%20Europa%2C%20which%20has%20twice%20as%20much%20water%20as%20Earth%20beneath%20its%20crust.%26quot%3B%20The%20planet%20GJ%209827d%20could%20be%20half%20water%2C%20half%20rock.%20And%20there%20would%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20water%20vapour%20on%20top%20of%20some%20smaller%20rocky%20body%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Benneke.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706457720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fopv6i9kg_exoplanet_625x300_28_January_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasas-hubble-telescope-detects-water-vapour-in-small-exoplanets-atmosphere-4949159%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20findings%20of%20the%20study%20appeared%20in%20a%20report%20published%20on%20Thursday%20in%20The%20Astrophysical%20Journal%20Letters.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasas-hubble-telescope-detects-water-vapour-in-small-exoplanets-atmosphere-4949159%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F