22title%22%3A%22Yashpal%20reveals%20he%20liked%20Lakha'more%20than%20Bhuvan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706435366000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107203182%2Cimgsize-30774.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fyashpal-sharma-on-why-he-preferred-lakha-over-aamir-khans-bhuvan-in-lagaan%2Farticleshow%2F107203182.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107203182.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAamir%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20iconic%20film%20'Lagaan'%20swept%20the%20nation%2C%20and%20even%20made%20it%20to%20the%20Oscars%20shortlist%20in%20the%20Foreign%20Language%20category%20in%202002%2C%20but%20unfortunately%20it%20didn't%20win%20the%20honour.%20However%2C%20the%20film%20is%20still%20loved%20and%20rewatched%20by%20many.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fyashpal-sharma-on-why-he-preferred-lakha-over-aamir-khans-bhuvan-in-lagaan%2Farticleshow%2F107203182.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%221%2C480%20Square%20Yards%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09172250%2FBabri-Masjid.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20actual%20disputed%20site%20on%20which%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20stood%20was%201%2C480%20square%20yards%20in%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20amount%20to%20less%20than%20many%20houses%20in%20Delhi%20and%20elsewhere.%20Clearly%2C%20no%20%3Cem%3Emandir%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20any%20consequence%20could%20have%20been%20built%20there.%20True%2C%20the%20legal%20dispute%20sprawled%20to%20the%202.77%20acres%20taken%20over%20by%20the%20state%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flddashboard.legislative.gov.in%2Factsofparliamentfromtheyear%2Facquisition-certain-area-ayodhya-act-1993%5C%22%3EAcquisition%20of%20Certain%20Area%20at%C2%A0Ayodhya%20Act%2C%201993%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20the%20actual%20size%20was%20just%201%2C480%20square%20yards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20might%20legitimately%20argue%20what%20the%20controversy%20was%20about.%20The%20temple%20necessarily%20had%20to%20be%20built%20on%20the%20surrounding%20land%20already%20owned%20by%20the%20Sangh%20%3Cem%3Eparivar%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20where%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20now%20sprawls%20over%20a%20huge%20area%2C%20not%20in%20dispute.%20Nor%20can%20it%20be%20said%20that%20the%20inner%20sanctum%20representing%20Lord%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20birth%20was%20placed%20exactly%20where%20the%20masjid%20was%20%E2%80%93%20as%20vehemently%20argued%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncidentally%2C%20the%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India%20(ASI)%E2%80%99s%20report%20to%20the%20court%20stated%20that%20it%20could%20not%20be%20conclusively%20said%20that%20Babur%20destroyed%20the%20temple%20to%20build%20a%20mosque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20history%20of%20the%20contestation%20dates%20back%20to%201857-8.%20It%20was%20futile%20to%20examine%20whether%20Muslims%20had%20possession%20before%201857.%20We%20must%20presume%20that%20they%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hindu%20counter%20trespass%20in%201857-8%20found%20an%20encroachment%20to%20parts%20of%20the%20site.%20In%201885%2C%20the%20Commissioner%E2%80%99s%20Court%20authoritatively%20held%20that%20the%20Muslims%20had%20title%2C%20and%20the%20Hindus%20had%2C%20at%20best%2C%20a%20prescriptive%20right%20to%20worship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%20latter%20period%2C%20Muslims%20had%20access%20to%20the%20masjid%20even%20though%20attempts%20were%20made%20in%201935-6%20to%20damage%20the%20mosque.%20The%20Hindus%20had%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20repair%20which%20was%20made%20by%20Muslims.%20This%20attempt%20to%20take%20the%20masjid%20by%20force%20and%20injure%20it%20was%20nothing%20new%20and%20culminated%20in%20its%20destruction%20in%201992.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fayodhya-rss-bjp-vhp-ram-temple%5C%22%3EFour%20Decades%20of%20Milking%20a%20Deity%20in%20Ayodhya%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20Hindus%20continued%20to%20pray%20to%20the%20idol%20which%20%E2%80%93%20according%20to%20the%20Hindus%20%E2%80%93%20miraculously%20appeared%20in%20December%201949%2C%20it%20was%20due%20to%20court%20orders%20and%20could%20not%20give%20them%20title%20which%20was%20equally%20miraculously%20given%20to%20them%20in%20November%202019%20by%20the%20final%20judgment%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20If%20the%20judgment%20is%20taken%20at%20face%20value%2C%20the%20masjid%20was%20destroyed%20in%201992%20on%20Hindu%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20verdict%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202019%20was%20shaky.%20Suit%20no.%205%20was%C2%A0filed%20in%201989%20and%20clearly%20outside%20limitation%20%E2%80%93%20even%20if%20we%20take%20December%201961%2C%20when%20the%20Sunni%20Board%20filed%20its%20case%20claiming%20title%2C%20as%20the%20start%20of%20the%20dispute.%20The%20limitation%20period%20is%2012%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20Hindu%20suit%20of%201989%20was%20well%20within%20limitation.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20justification%20was%20that%20by%20virtue%20of%20the%20deity%20not%20being%20party%20in%20the%20earlier%20suits%2C%20its%20interests%20were%20not%20being%20adequately%20protected%20in%20the%20earlier%20suits%20including%20those%20initiated%20by%20the%20Hindu%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Mahant%E2%80%99s%20case%20of%201959%20was%20to%20defend%20the%20Hindu%20cause%2C%20and%20did%20not%20claim%20title%20and%20was%20declared%20outside%20limitation.%20In%20a%20terse%20summation%20on%20the%201989%20suit%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20declared%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Creasons%20which%20weighed%20with%20Agarwal%20J.%20(in%20the%20High%20Court)%2C%20as%20summarised%20above%2C%20commend%20themselves%20for%20acceptance%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENever%20was%20the%20question%20of%20limitation%20so%20sparsely%20disposed%20of.%20Nor%20can%20it%20be%20said%20that%20the%20title%20and%20possession%20were%20not%20with%20the%20Muslims%20at%20the%20time%20of%20trespass%20in%20December%201949%2C%20as%20advocate%20Zafaryab%20Jilani%20convincingly%20demonstrated%20to%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%20was%20an%20expensive%20farce.%20The%20farce%20was%20exacerbated%20recently%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20not%20applying%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mha.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FPlaceWorshipAct1991.pdf%5C%22%3EPlaces%20of%20Worship%20(Special%20Provision)%20Act%2C%201991%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20the%20present%20case%20involving%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%20in%20Varanasi.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sci.gov.in%2Fpdf%2FJUD_2.pdf%5C%22%3EIn%20its%20Ayodhya%20judgement%20of%20November%209%2C%202019%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20said%20the%201991%20Act%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%20enforced%20a%20constitutional%20commitment%20and%20operationalised%20its%20constitutional%20obligations%20to%20uphold%20the%20equality%20of%20all%20religions%20and%20secularism%20which%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20basic%20features%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20imposes%20a%20non-derogable%20obligation%20towards%20enforcing%20our%20commitment%20to%20secularism%20under%20the%20Indian%20Constitution.%20The%20law%20is%20hence%20a%20legislative%20instrument%20designed%20to%20protect%20the%20secular%20features%20of%20the%20Indian%20polity%2C%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20basic%20features%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20Non-retrogression%20is%20a%20foundational%20feature%20of%20the%20fundamental%20constitutional%20principles%20of%20which%20secularism%20is%20a%20core%20component.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%2C%201991%20is%20thus%20a%20legislative%20intervention%20which%20preserves%20non-retrogression%20as%20an%20essential%20feature%20of%20our%20secular%20values.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhy-the-places-of-worship-act-must-be-preserved%5C%22%3EWhy%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20Must%20Be%20Preserved%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20this%20was%20what%20the%201991%20Act%20said%20according%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20what%20happened%20to%20all%20this%20in%20its%20application%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fayodhya-mathura-varanasi-why-the-coming-week-is-crucial-for-the-hindutva-project%5C%22%3Econtroversies%20over%20Varanasi%20and%20now%20Mathura%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20many%20things%20in%20the%20Babri%20decisions%20were%20fudged%2C%20even%20though%20the%202019%20judgement%20was%20seen%20as%20liberation.%C2%A0We%20can%20re-write%20history%20but%20not%20ignore%20its%20fundamentals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20political%20appropriation%20of%20Lord%20Ram%20in%20Ayodhya%20is%20a%20thorn%20in%20the%20side%20of%20our%20governance.%20It%20is%20true%20that%20we%20do%20not%20follow%20the%20strict%20American%20doctrine%20of%20separation%20of%20state%20from%20religion.%20But%20India%20does%20not%20reject%20that%20doctrine.%20If%20we%20follow%20the%20doctrine%20of%20principled%20equality%2C%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20token%20visit%20to%20Muslim%20sites%20does%20not%20make%20the%20cut.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20to%20realise%20that%20India%20is%20not%20a%20Hindu%20state%20fuelled%20by%20Hindutva.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20wholly%20wrong%20when%20it%20ruled%20in%201995%20that%20Hindutva%20is%20not%20an%20appeal%20to%20religion%20in%20elections.%20This%20aggressive%20Hinduism%20is%20a%20step%20towards%20the%20Hinduisation%20of%20India%2C%20which%20is%20not%20an%20exercise%20in%20secularism%20but%20a%20political%20declaration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20been%20complicit%20in%20this%20process%2C%20but%20it%20must%20otherwise%20also%20realise%20that%20it%20is%20unconstitutional%20to%20support%20a%20Hindu%20elected%20dictatorship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Babri%20case%20and%20its%20inelegant%20aftermath%20have%20witnessed%20a%20crack%20in%20our%20polity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECelebrate%20Lord%20Ram%20by%20all%20means%2C%20but%20using%20the%20state%20to%20spend%20from%20its%20coffers%20in%20this%20celebration%20is%20far%20from%20appropriate%2C%20because%20it%20is%20dangerously%20divisive%2C%20as%20indeed%20was%20the%20%3Cem%3Erath%20yatra%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20claim%20these%201%2C480%20square%20yards%20for%20which%20history%20was%20defiled%20and%20a%20tradition%20of%20healthy%20secularism%20abandoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20people%20develop%20this%20site%20not%20through%20politics.%20Will%20the%20same%20hype%20accompany%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fno-sign-of-new-ayodhya-mosque%5C%22%3Ethe%20masjid%20in%20Ayodhya%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20it%20is%20built%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20the%20most%20diverse%20country%20in%20the%20world%2C%20more%20than%20many%20continents.%20It%20is%20this%20diversity%20that%20makes%20us%20unique.%20To%20abandon%20it%20destroys%20the%20India%20that%20is%20to%20be%20treasured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Frajeev-dhavan%2F%5C%22%3ERajeev%20Dhavan%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20advocate%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20He%20has%20represented%20Muslim%20parties%20in%20the%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi-Babri%20Masjid%20title%20dispute%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706434983000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2