%20free%20press%2C%20free%20speech%20and%20creative%20freedom%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20press%20release%2C%20the%20NWMI%20said%20it%20submitted%20a%20%E2%80%9Cclause-by-clause%20analysis%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Bill%20to%20the%20government%20in%20which%20it%20flagged%20issues%20such%20as%20vague%20definitions%2C%20opaque%20regulations%20and%20overriding%20powers%20proposed%20for%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20its%20concerns%20are%20that%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Cnews%20and%20current%20affairs%20programmes%E2%80%9D%20will%20allow%20it%20to%20regulate%20YouTubers%20and%20citizen%20journalists%2C%20that%20opacity%20around%20the%20Bill%E2%80%99s%20regulations%20would%20prompt%20creators%20to%20%E2%80%9Cavoid%20risk-taking%20at%20all%20costs%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Cself-certification%E2%80%9D%20regime%20proposed%20by%20the%20Bill%20amounted%20to%20the%20government%20%E2%80%9Crunning%20editorial%20panels%20to%20monitor%20content%20being%20generated%20by%20broadcasters%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20cautioned%20that%20the%20government%20must%20not%20go%20ahead%20with%20the%20Bill%20without%20exhaustive%20consultations%20with%20stakeholders%20and%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Chaste%20with%20which%20the%20Bill%20has%20been%20drafted%20and%20announced%20to%20the%20public%2C%20and%20the%20limited%20time%20provided%20for%20responses%2C%20is%20unacceptable%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1059881%2Fwhy-indias-new-draft-broadcast-bill-has-raised-fears-of-censorship-and-press-suppression%5C%22%3EMedia%20experts%20and%20news%20editors%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20also%20expressed%20their%20concerns%20with%20the%20Bill.%20The%20Editors%E2%80%99%20Guild%20of%20India%20said%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20the%20Bill%E2%80%99s%20regulatory%20framework%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fvague-and-excessively-intrusive-editors-guild-of-india-to-centre-on-broadcast-services-bill%5C%22%3Elaid%20the%20foundations%20for%20an%20%E2%80%9Coverarching%20censorship%20framework%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20information%20and%20broadcasting%20ministry%20began%20soliciting%20the%20public%E2%80%99s%20feedback%20on%20the%20draft%20Bill%20on%20November%2010%20last%20year.%20The%20last%20date%20for%20providing%20feedback%20was%20December%209.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fparliamentry-announcement%2F2023-12-09%2FDraft_Broadcasting_Services_(Regulation)_Bill%2C_2023.pdf%5C%22%3EThe%20text%20of%20the%20draft%20can%20be%20read%20here%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NWMI%E2%80%99s%20full%20statement%20is%20reproduced%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Network%20of%20Women%20in%20Media%2C%20India%20(NWMI)%2C%20has%20made%20a%20detailed%20submission%20to%20the%20Central%20Government%20regarding%20the%20proposed%20Broadcasting%20Services%20(Regulation)%20Bill%202023%20that%20was%20published%20by%20the%20Information%20and%20Broadcasting%20Ministry%20to%20get%20feedback%20from%20the%20public%20and%20all%20stake-holders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Broadcasting%20Bill%20seeks%20to%20replace%20the%20Cable%20Television%20Networks%20(Regulation)%20Act%20of%201995%2C%20with%20the%20stated%20objective%20of%20providing%20a%20comprehensive%20regulatory%20regime%20for%20all%20forms%20of%20broadcasting%20content%20from%20television%20to%20streaming%20platforms.%20In%20its%20letter%20to%20the%20Ministry%2C%20NWMI%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20government%20bestows%20inordinate%20powers%20on%20itself%20through%20this%20Bill%20to%20control%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20entertainment%20and%20news%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20intent%20to%20control%20and%20over-regulate%20is%20not%20in%20the%20interests%20of%20a%20healthy%2C%20independent%20media%20or%20a%20thriving%20culture%20of%20entertainment.%20It%20goes%20against%20the%20very%20foundations%20of%20media%20freedom%20in%20mature%20democracies%20everywhere%20and%20will%20irreparably%20damage%20the%20free%20press%2C%20free%20speech%20and%20creative%20freedom%20in%20India%2C%20NWMI%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20this%20Bill%20could%20potentially%20drastically%20alter%20the%20media%20landscape%20in%20India%2C%20NWMI%20has%20exhorted%20the%20government%20to%20not%2C%20under%20any%20circumstances%2C%20proceed%20with%20it%20without%20exhaustive%20discussions%20among%20the%20key%20stake-holders%20involved.%20Considering%20its%20far-reaching%20implications%2C%20NWMI%20said%20the%20haste%20with%20which%20the%20Bill%20has%20been%20drafted%20and%20announced%20to%20the%20public%2C%20and%20the%20limited%20time%20provided%20for%20responses%2C%20is%20unacceptable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20clause-by-clause%20analysis%20submitted%20to%20the%20government%2C%20NWMI%20has%20flagged%20several%20concerns%20that%20are%20summarised%20below%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(1)%20The%20draft%20Bill%E2%80%99s%20vaguely%20worded%20provisions%2C%20including%20its%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Cnews%20and%20current%20affairs%20programmes%E2%80%9D%2C%20arm%20it%20with%20the%20potential%20to%20cover%20individual%20Youtubers%2C%20the%20social%20media%20accounts%20of%20professional%20journalists%20and%20even%20citizen%20journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(2)%20The%20Bill%20places%20requirements%20and%20burdens%20on%20news%20organisations%20that%2C%20while%20cumbersome%20for%20large%20broadcasting%20networks%2C%20could%20potentially%20put%20small%20news%20operators%20out%20of%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(3)%20The%20Broadcasting%20Bill%20mentions%20a%20Programme%20Code%20and%20an%20Advertising%20Code%20%E2%80%9Cas%20may%20be%20prescribed%E2%80%9D.%20Any%20public%20consultation%20on%20the%20Bill%20is%20meaningless%20unless%20the%20government%20publishes%20an%20outline%20of%20the%20proposed%20codes%20and%20seeks%20feedback%20on%20those%20codes%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(4)%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20clearly%20defined%20codes%20available%20along%20with%20the%20draft%20Bill%2C%20the%20publication%20of%20the%20draft%20Bill%20in%20itself%20will%20have%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20creators%20of%20entertainment%20and%20news%20content%20who%20will%20be%20driven%2C%20if%20not%20by%20their%20own%20fears%20and%20prevailing%20uncertainty%2C%20then%20by%20the%20management%20of%20their%20organisations%2C%20to%20avoid%20risk-taking%20at%20all%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(5)%20The%20Bill%20shows%20a%20lack%20of%20understanding%20not%20just%20of%20what%20constitutes%20news%2C%20but%20also%20of%20the%20functioning%20of%20news%20organisations%20when%20it%20seeks%20to%20club%20them%20with%20creators%20of%20entertainment%20content%2C%20especially%20considering%20the%20provision%20to%20subject%20the%20work%20of%20newspersons%20to%20Content%20Evaluation%20Committees%20(CECs).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(6)%20The%20Bill%20lays%20out%20a%20system%20of%20%E2%80%9Cself-certification%E2%80%9D%20by%20CECs%20that%20are%20to%20be%20constituted%20by%20all%20broadcasters%20and%20broadcasting%20networks%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bill.%20However%2C%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Cself-certification%E2%80%9D%20is%20a%20misnomer%20since%20the%20Bill%20gives%20the%20Central%20Government%20an%20overriding%20role%20in%20the%20formation%20of%20CECs%20and%20amounts%20to%20the%20government%20running%20editorial%20panels%20to%20monitor%20content%20being%20generated%20by%20broadcasters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(7)%20The%20Bill%20places%20unreasonable%20curbs%20on%20news%20and%20entertainment%20organisations%20that%20will%20inevitably%20hamper%20their%20functioning%20at%20a%20very%20fundamental%20level%20and%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20make%20it%20financially%20unviable%20for%20small%2C%20independent%20news%20set-ups%20to%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(8)%20In%20the%20context%20of%20OTT%20platforms%2C%20CECs%20look%20set%20to%20mimic%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20Central%20Board%20of%20Film%20Certification%20(CBFC%2C%20known%20in%20popular%20parlance%20as%20the%20Censor%20Board)%2C%20a%20statutory%20body%20that%20has%20been%20criticised%20and%20opposed%20by%20generations%20of%20Indian%20filmmakers.%20Among%20other%20things%2C%20bringing%20OTTs%20under%20such%20CBFC-like%20bodies%20defies%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20Committee%20of%20Experts%20constituted%20by%20this%20government%20and%20chaired%20by%20the%20renowned%20filmmaker%20Shyam%20Benegal%2C%20that%20had%20called%20for%20a%20more%20liberalised%20certification%20system%20even%20for%20films.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(9)%20The%20Central%20Government%E2%80%99s%20overarching%20role%20in%20the%20functioning%20of%20news%20and%20entertainment%20media%20as%20per%20the%20provisions%20of%20this%20Bill%20is%20further%20enhanced%20by%20the%20requirement%20for%20the%20formation%20of%20a%20Broadcast%20Advisory%20Council%2C%20the%20composition%20of%20which%20will%20primarily%20be%20determined%20by%20the%20Central%20Government.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706430042000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07112943%2FScreenshot-2023-09-07-at-11.28.4.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fintent-to-overregulate-media-behind-draft-broadcast-bill-irreprable-damage-nwmi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Vague%20definitions%2C%20opaque%20regulations%20and%20overriding%20powers%20proposed%20for%20the%20Union%20government%20were%20among%20the%20concerns%20the%20NWMI%20said%20it%20flagged%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20while%20providing%20feedback%20on%20the%20draft%20Bill.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fintent-to-overregulate-media-behind-draft-broadcast-bill-irreprable-damage-nwmi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Dev%E2%80%99s%20Monkey%20Man%20was%20to%20release%20direct