referrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F310812%2Fmukul-chhabra-scrapuncle-delhi-startup-collects-recycles-scrap-wins-lakhs-shark-tank%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20scrap%20dealers%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20will%20take%20that%20amount%20of%20plastic.%20I%20realised%20that%20this%20was%20a%20problem%20with%20many%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20push%20people%20to%20make%20segregating%20waste%20a%20habit%20and%20part%20of%20their%20daily%20routine%2C%20Abhishek%20decided%20to%20give%20them%20an%20incentive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20how%20the%20idea%20behind%20Goodeebag%20came%20about%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fycharit-9-1706017651.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Abhishek%20Agarwal%2C%20Founder%20of%20Goodeebag.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fycharit-9-1706017651.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fycharit-9-1706017651-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fycharit-9-1706017651-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fycharit-9-1706017651-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fycharit-9-1706017651-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-339597%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAbhishek%20Agarwal%2C%20Founder%20of%20Goodeebag.%20Picture%20credit%3A%20Goodeebag%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Something%20for%20Nothing%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20passion%20for%20me%20more%20than%20anything%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says%2C%20recalling%20how%20his%20friends%20and%20family%20reacted%20when%20he%20decided%20to%20start%20the%20company.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20were%20not%20as%20excited%20as%20I%20was.%20I%20had%20an%20existing%20business%20that%20was%20doing%20well%20and%20there%20was%20no%20need%20to%20switch.%20They%20would%20think%20that%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20it%20is%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Kabaad%20ka%20business%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20(scrap%20business).%20It%20was%20my%20passion%20towards%20nature%20conservation%20that%20kept%20me%20going%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbhishek%20feels%20that%20it%20is%20not%20just%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20responsibility%20to%20manage%20waste%20but%20ours%20too.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20concept%20of%20giving%20away%20rewards%20comes%20from%20my%20basic%20understanding%20of%20human%20nature.%20We%20all%20love%20free%20stuff%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20we%3F%20So%20the%20reward%20system%20has%20worked%20perfectly%20for%20us%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20how%20his%20company%20works%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20simple%20%E2%80%94%20we%20have%20an%20app%20which%20a%20consumer%20downloads.%20They%20segregate%20their%20waste%20and%20schedule%20a%20visit%20from%20the%20app.%20Our%20collection%20executive%20comes%20and%20picks%20up%20their%20waste.%20The%20consumer%20can%20go%20to%20the%20application%20and%20collect%20their%20reward%20points.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20application%20has%20a%20variety%20of%20products%20that%20consumers%20can%20buy.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20usually%20have%20household%20stuff%20and%20groceries%20which%20the%20consumers%20can%20buy%20for%20free.%20We%20deliver%20them%20to%20their%20homes%20within%2072%20hours%20without%20a%20delivery%20charge.%20So%20basically%2C%20you%20get%20something%20for%20nothing%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%