EHer%20parents%20stood%20by%20her%20like%20rocks%20through%20this%20entire%20ordeal.%20Her%20father%20quit%20his%20job%20to%20take%20care%20of%20her%20and%20they%20moved%20to%20Tiruvannamalai%2C%20a%20spiritual%2C%20temple%20town%2C%20to%20heal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPreethi%20then%20tried%20to%20get%20admission%20to%20a%20correspondence%20course%20for%20BSc%20Psychology%2C%20but%20she%20was%20rejected%20as%20there%20were%20practical%20classes%20and%20the%20colleges%20were%20not%20disabled-friendly.%20There%20were%20no%20elevators%20or%20ramps.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20remembers%20being%20asked%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20do%20people%20like%20you%20come%20to%20study%3F%E2%80%9D%20Her%20father%2C%20her%20biggest%20cheerleader%2C%20bought%20her%20books%20to%20study%2C%20and%20motivated%20her%20to%20educate%20herself%2C%20degree%2C%20or%20no%20degree.%20He%20would%20read%20out%20to%20her%20from%20various%20books%20across%20genres%2C%20from%20fiction%20to%20educational%20books%20to%20spiritual%20books.%20She%20would%20fight%20with%20him%2C%20but%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20let%20go%20of%20her%20hand%2C%20and%20helped%20her%20overcome%20her%20pain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20she%20started%20piecing%20her%20life%20together%2C%20another%20big%20wave%20hit%20her.%20Her%20father%20died%20of%20a%20heart%20attack%20in%202007%2C%20and%20just%20four%20days%20later%2C%20her%20mother%2C%20too%2C%20had%20a%20heart%20attack%20and%20had%20to%20have%20a%20bypass%20surgery.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20world%20was%20rocked%20again.%20I%20had%20an%2080-year-old%20grandmother%20to%20take%20care%20of.%20We%20had%20to%20go%20to%20Chennai%20for%20the%20surgery.%20We%20had%20no%20idea%20how%20we%20would%20manage%20the%20next%20meal%20or%20who%20would%20even%20help%20me%20sit%20on%20my%20wheelchair.%20I%20had%20to%20start%20earning%20money%20and%20life%20seemed%20difficult%20all%20over%20again%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Preethi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20point%2C%20her%20